# CODEOWNERS — knovya-labs/knovya-crypto
#
# Lines in this file assign default reviewers to paths. GitHub
# automatically requests review from the owners when a pull request
# modifies a matching file.
#
# Until the public launch, the `@knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers`
# team is a placeholder. The real team is created on GitHub in the
# hour before the repository is made public, with the founding
# maintainer as initial owner. Subsequent maintainers are added by
# explicit PR.
#
# Syntax reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owner for anything in the repo
*                               @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers

# Cryptographic surface — extra review sensitivity
/crypto/                        @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers
/crypto/types.ts                @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers
/crypto/frontend/               @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers
/crypto/backend/                @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers

# Security policy and disclosure channel
/SECURITY.md                    @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers
/.github/SECURITY.md            @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers
/PGP-PUBLIC-KEY.asc             @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers

# CI workflows — a bad edit here can silently disable the audit gate
/.github/workflows/             @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers

# Whitepaper + audit history — any change must be reviewed by a maintainer
# with whitepaper context.
/docs/whitepaper/               @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers
/docs/audit-history.md          @knovya-labs/crypto-maintainers
